.TH SIDEQUEST 1
.SH NAME
sidequest \- play a tiny terminal game while waiting for a command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sidequest
.RI [ options ]
.B --
.I command
.RI [ arguments... ]
.PP
.B sidequest list
.PP
.B sidequest attach
.I session-id
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sidequest
runs a command in one tmux pane and opens a small terminal game in another.
When the command finishes, the game freezes and Sidequest shows the command
state, exit code or signal, runtime, and final score.
.PP
Commands are executed directly. Arguments after
.B --
are preserved as an argument vector and are not passed through a shell.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help text.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show the Sidequest version.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List Sidequest runtime sessions.
.TP
.BI attach " session-id"
Attach to an existing Sidequest tmux session.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B F12
Switch between the command pane and the game pane.
.TP
.B F10
Detach from the Sidequest tmux session and return to the shell.
.TP
.B WASD or arrow keys
Start and control Snake in the game pane.
.TP
.B P
Pause or resume the game.
.TP
.B Q
Leave the game pane. The command pane is not killed.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Sidequest requires Linux and
.BR tmux (1)
at runtime.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/sidequest
Installed Sidequest executable.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/sidequest/
Installed license and README documentation.
.TP
.I /usr/share/man/man1/sidequest.1
Installed manual page.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Sidequest returns zero when setup and attach handling succeed. The command
runner records the child command result in Sidequest session metadata.
.SH BUGS
Report issues at
.UR https://github.com/WBT112/sidequest/issues
.UE
